/* Phosphate */  Deletion of inaccurate statement. The statement that bones and teeth are the primary source of PO4 is fantastical. Algal deposition in shallow seas, followed by burial and preservation due to anoxia in the sediments, is the primary source of phosphate minerals. Bones and teeth certainly do contain phosphate, but their total contribution to P is a rounding error.
